    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The prompt is a matter of taste. pdb's prompt is `(Pdb) ` and when you invoke it recursively, it changes into `((Pdb)) ` with more parentheses added for each level of recursion. ipdb uses `ipdb> ` and since I left that calculation as is, it will use `(ipdb>) ` when invoked recursively. Unless you prefer some other prompt for the recursive invocation, than this PR is ready."
